<D>__{by now, young brookside was of so wild, savage, and insubordinate a nature that i never had the least regard for him. as he grew up to be a man, his hatred for me assumed an intensity quite wicked to think of and which, i promise you, i returned with interest.}
<A>__{he drags brookside into his study, slamming the door behind him.}
